been considerable, we have decided to separate reports into different
posting threads. In this report we are focusing on the numbers of cases
reported and transmission. Information on the identification of the
etiologic agent and development of specific diagnostic tests will be
covered separately as has been done by the issuing of separate "stand
alone" posts in the past week. To allow room for more informative titles,
we will now use the generally accepted acronym SARS for severe acute
respiratory syndrome and add qualifiers to the subject line. - Mod.MPP]
